    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hi @altaurog,\r\n\r\nFor this, I copied the behaviour of Vi. The reason is that we support multiline editing. So, if you're at the start of a multiline buffer, then you could use forward search to jump forward. In a block of multiline text, you'll get more of the Vi feel, rather than a readline feeling.\r\n\r\nBut maybe you're right. It could make sense to follow GNU readline, and use question mark to search forward.\r\n\r\nCould you open an issue in prompt_toolkit? Maybe I could make this easier to configure, or if I feel that everyone thinks it should be like readline, then I could reverse it."
  },
