    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I just want to mention that if you would like the old (IPython <= 4.x) readline interface, it is now available separately as [rlipython](https://github.com/ipython/rlipython). \r\n\r\n```\r\npip install rlipython\r\npython -c \"import rlipython as r; r.install()\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nRight now, it only works in IPython 6.0 (Python 3), but it will also work in Python 2 with the next IPython 5 release (5.4)."
